Building on Unix with gcc and autotools

Home page for xlog:
	https://github.com/HardySimpson/xlog

If checking out from Git (https://github.com/HardySimpson/xlog):

    $ sh autogen.sh

Then 

    $ ./configure
    $ make
    $ make install

To build and run the test programs run 

    $ make check
    $ cd test

Then run all the test program under test directory and see output

Linking to libxlog

If your system has pkgconfig then you can just add this to your makefile

CFLAGS += $(shell pkg-config --cflags xlog)
LDFLAGS += $(shell pkg-config --libs xlog)
